                </a>]]></description></item><item><title>Toys for Kids</title><dc:creator>Tiffany Fairdosi</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 19 Feb 2026 18:11:30 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.kineticspeech.com/blog/qxo546434kqnjbgfts8vwagmwia0lg</link><guid isPermaLink="false">644281148cd62262058dd198:6445cff5e468036516f44b30:69962e0aec82966b9e8c5460</guid><description><![CDATA[<p class="">Here at Kinetic Speech Services, we offer therapy to children and adults. We keep our offices separate to ensure comfort for the different age groups. In today’s post, we wanted to share a few items you might find in our pediatric office space!</p><p class="">We think play time is the best time! We encourage social interactions, making valuable and meaningful connections, and engagement with your child. We follow the child’s needs in whatever way their play time looks like whether that is stacking toys together, looking at the cars go by, or teaching them how to be good sportsman during a board game.</p><p class="">Here are 5 toys for our littlest of friends we would totally recommend for having in the home! If you sneeked a peak, you might find these in our office or even in our homes. Now that MY kids are bigger, we don’t have half as many toys as we used to. Likely, some of these toys even came from my house before being repurposed here! They are loved and cherished and hold so much meaning to me. I can’t wait to share!</p>


  















































  

    
  
    

      

      
