<p><a href="https://www.kineticspeech.com/blog/qxo546434kqnjbgfts8vwagmwia0lg">Permalink</a><p>]]></description></item><item><title>Glossary</title><dc:creator>Tiffany Fairdosi</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 03 Jun 2024 14:07:29 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.kineticspeech.com/blog/special-terms</link><guid isPermaLink="false">644281148cd62262058dd198:6445cff5e468036516f44b30:665dcb30d405f81f814b8ec4</guid><description><![CDATA[<p class="">Speech therapy is a world full of big words. Let’s break down some of the big words.</p><p class=""><strong>Dysphagia:</strong> Swallowing impairments that can you can be born with or acquire after a life changing event</p><p class=""><strong>Augmentative-alternative communication device:</strong> a special device used to generate spoken words at the click of a button. Can be very robust!</p><p class=""><strong>Aphasia:</strong> language loss typically after a stroke but can be a result of other neurological changes</p><p class=""><strong>Phonological Processes:</strong> Speech sound patterns present in the years we learn to speak that should eventually go away</p><p class="">As time goes on, more special terms will be added to the glossary. I will add blog posts on special events, certain terms, and highlight accomplishments from us at Kinetic Speech Services.</p><p class="">We value you and your families more than you know and appreciate your feedback! </p><p class="">Please like and follow us on our social media pages and leave us a review on Google.</p>]]></description></item></channel></rss>